react in vscode
1. go to vite official website and copy npm script i.e.: npm create vite@latest 
2. open vscode create a new folder you can name it like anything
3. then open new terminal and paste the npm scipt there 
if comes error cannot be loaded because running scripts is disabled on this system then follow step4
4. open powershell and type : Get-ExecutionPolicy and if it is restricted 
   then type : Set-ExecutionPolicy Unrestricted
   and even then error comes like  : Access to the registry key 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\PowerShell\1\ShellIds\Microsoft.PowerShell' is denied.
   then open powershell as run as administrator
   and then type: Set-ExecutionPolicy Unrestricted
   then option will pop up so i typed A 
   and now open vscode and in terminal type : npm create vite@latest
5. after running npm create vite@latest in terminal
   give permission to proceed
   you can any name of project
   then you will be asked for framework so selet react 
   then choose a varient whichever you are suitable with i am with js
6. you will see option to install npm and start now
   but if not then type in termial: cd vite
   then : npm install
   then type : npm run dev    and then click on the localhost link and if it shows the react icon then you react is now ready

note: so vite is not only way to install react there are many but as per now it is recommended to vite for react.
